<emphasis box="[1254,1313,1560,1585]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1320,1383,1560,1586]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,1597,1623]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Panesar" box="[288,476,1597,1623]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Panesar, A. (2004) Evolution in water mites (Hydrachnellae, Actinedida, Acari). A revision of the Anisitsiellidae Koenike, 1910. Bonner Zoologische Monographien, 52, 1 - 144." type="journal article" year="2004">
Panesar (
<number box="[402,467,1597,1623]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName box="[599,811,1597,1622]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Nilotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turcica">
<emphasis box="[599,811,1597,1622]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Nilotonia turcica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[1023,1105,1597,1622]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Dartia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1023,1105,1597,1622]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Dartia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However according to Di Sabatino 
<emphasis box="[261,313,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[336,398,1634,1660]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2010.0">2010</number>
) the lacking of the sexual dimorphism of II-L (characteristic for the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[1319,1426,1635,1660]" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Dartiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1319,1426,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Dartiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is of a greater taxonomic weight, while the reduced size of the Ac may have more easily evolved several times independently.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1522,1810]" box="[151,877,1746,1772]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,256,1746,1772]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Habitat:</emphasis>
